{"id":"333768878_Relevant_Parameters_for_the_Classification_of_Reading_Books_Depending_on_the_Degree_of_Textual_Readability_in_Primary_and_Compulsory_Secondary_Education_CSE_Students","abstract":"The present research tries to establish the most important parameters of readability when it comes to choosing reading books for students in the 2nd and 3rd stages of Primary and Compulsory Secondary Education (CSE). A computational system is postulated, through data-mining techniques, capable of automatically classify reading texts by virtue of syntactic, lexical, semantic and topological parameters regarding their overall content. The validity of this process is ensured through a careful selection by editorial experts used to accomplish the same validation task among different texts. The results in the automatic classification of the degree of readability reached in this research are promising; they allow to continue with a deeper investigation in this field of analysis with the purpose of progressing in the age rank studied, as well as in the text themes defining the corpus.","authors":["R. Gil Ortego","I. Martmnez Sanchez"],"meta":["June 2019IEEE Access PP(99):1-1","DOI:10.1109/ACCESS.2019.2922608"],"references":["314878749_Reading_comprehension_is_not_a_single_ability","312083271_Estrategias_de_aprendizaje_comprension_lectora_y_rendimiento_academico_en_Educacion_Secundaria","299508339_PROCESOS_COGNOSCITIVOS_BASICOS_ASOCIADOS_A_LAS_DIFICULTADES_EN_COMPRENSION_LECTORA_DE_ALUMNOS_DE_SECUNDARIA","287236258_How_Reading_Volume_Affects_Both_Reading_Fluency_and_Reading_Achievement","281434427_Niveles_de_comprension_lectora_en_alumnos_de_secundaria_Una_comparacion_por_topico","277264156_Controversia_entre_madurez_lectora_y_ensenanza_precoz_de_la_lectura_revision_historica_y_propuestas_actuales","271519664_EDUCACION_INCLUSIVA_Y_FACIL_LECTURA_LA_COMPRENSION_Y_EL_TEXTO_COMO_VIAS_PARA_LLEGAR_A_TODOS_NUESTROS_ESTUDIANTES_INCLUSIVE_EDUCATION_AND_EASY_READING_UNDERSTANDING_AND_TEXT_AS